Super Eagles goalkeeper, Maduka Okoye is optimistic about a good outing for Nigeria at the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations holding in Cameroon irrespective of the harsh weather condition in Garoua as the team face Pharaohs of Egypt today in their Group D opener. Okoye also clamoured for the support of Nigerians stating that the show of from the country can ginger the players in  the bid  for their  fourth continental  title.   Eagles ‘ll tame Salah,  says Simon     Ighalo officially  quits  2021 AFCON     Salah: we’ll do everything to beat Nigeria   “I really can’t wait. It is the only thing I am thinking about. All is great in my mind set and the spirit in the camp is good and we are all fit,” Okoye told NFF Tv. “The weather is quite hot during the day but at night, it is more comfortable. Everybody needs to get used to the new environment. We are almost two weeks of training together and I believe we are used to it. - Advertisement - “We need Nigerians support and love because we have a very good spirit and with them as the 12th man we can get gold. We need their support so that we can give our best to Nigeria.”